---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Café Athena — The Manual. A cookbook built by a home cook for one person: his wife Athena."
  currentPage="about"
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 md:py-28">

    <header class="mb-14">
      <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-[#6b6b7b] mb-4 block">About</span>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-[#1a1a2e] leading-tight">
        Café Athena
      </h1>
      <div class="w-12 h-0.5 bg-[#c9a96e] mt-6"></div>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none font-body text-[#1a1a2e]/80 leading-relaxed space-y-6">

      <img
        src="/images/author-headshot.webp"
        alt="Kevin Ward"
        class="float-right ml-8 mb-4 w-40 md:w-48 rounded-sm not-prose"
      />

      <p>
        Kevin is not a chef. He'll say so before you ask — not to manage expectations, but because the distinction actually matters. A chef cooks under pressure, for strangers, on someone else's terms. Kevin cooks for people he loves, in a kitchen he knows, because he wants to. He has been doing this his entire adult life.
      </p>

      <p>
        His culinary education happened at family tables, in friends' kitchens, and in books — Escoffier, Keller, Pépin — supplemented by years of footage from Jean-Pierre and Marco Pierre White. He has never staged, never cooked professionally. What he has is a serious reading habit, a lot of time at the stove, and a desire to understand why something works rather than just knowing that it does. That is exactly the orientation this project is created from.
      </p>

      <p>
        The name came before the project. Working from home meant he was there to cook — cooking for Athena, with Athena, was simply what they did. Somewhere after 2020, he started posting dinner photos on Facebook with a brief note about what he'd made — nothing formal, just a caption: "Tonight at Café Athena." The name carried more than it said — she is the reason the kitchen mattered, and Café Athena says so without explaining it.
      </p>

      <p>
        Over decades, recipes had accumulated — scrawled on index cards, pulled from cookbooks, written on whatever was at hand. He moved the archive to OneNote and ran it on an iPad in the kitchen — everything in one place, right there on the counter, easy to access. Then came a Smart Fridge with a built-in display, and OneNote no longer worked. Around the same time, he was working through AI certification classes. The two things converged: a specific problem and the tools to solve it properly. The solution was an AI-powered website and AI tools to improve every part of working with recipes and cooking. Café Athena – The Manual is the project that brought it all together — a new kind of resource for the home cook.
      </p>

      <p>
        Café Athena – The Manual is organized the way a professional kitchen operates: technique and foundation first in the Academy chapters, then stations across the Brigade each one representing a key area of cooking, then the building-block preparations and components of the Larder. A cook who reads through The Academy understands why things happen at the stove. A cook who works through The Larder has a refrigerator full of preparations that make every Brigade recipe compound. The Manual is designed so that nothing you learn here stops with the recipe where you learned it.
      </p>

      <figure class="clear-both mt-12 not-prose">
        <img
          src="/images/Kevin_Ward-Athena_Blanton-Monterey-California.webp"
          alt="Kevin Ward and Athena Blanton, Monterey, California"
          class="w-full"
        />
        <figcaption class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[#6b6b7b] mt-3 text-center">
          Kevin Ward and Athena Blanton — Monterey, California
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

    </div>

    <nav class="mt-16 pt-10 border-t border-[#e0d8cc] flex flex-wrap gap-6">
      <a href="/academy" class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[#6b6b7b] hover:text-[#c9a96e] transition-colors">The Academy →</a>
      <a href="/brigade" class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[#6b6b7b] hover:text-[#c9a96e] transition-colors">The Brigade →</a>
      <a href="/larder" class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[#6b6b7b] hover:text-[#c9a96e] transition-colors">The Larder →</a>
    </nav>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
